        "headline": "Special Weather Statement issued June 7 at 9:37PM MDT by NWS Aberdeen SD",
        "description": "At 937 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near\nThunder Hawk, or 10 miles southeast of Lemmon, moving northeast at 30\nmph.\n\nHAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.\n\nSOURCE...Radar indicated.\n\nIMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around\nunsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is\npossible.\n\nLocations impacted include...\nMorristown, Watauga, Keldron, and Thunder Hawk.",
        "instruction": "If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.\n\nA Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until midnight MDT for\nnorth central South Dakota.",
